Time has not done this attraction any favours. When I first visited (about 15 years ago) you went down the narrow entrance and had a good "window" looking out to sea and felt the magic of the place. Now, the rocks have tumbled and I can't believe it's a safe place to go. It seems like an accident waiting to happen.
View of Ramla Bay from Mixta Cave. High up on the opposite side overlooking the bay lies Calypso‚Äôs Cave which is believed to have housed the nymph in Homer‚Äôs Odyssey.
The goverment is thinking about to restore the view as it was, I hope they do it quickly, because it was allways a great view.

Calypso Cave is situated in Xaghra and overlooks the red sands of Gozo's Ramla beach. It is alleged to be the cave referred to by Homer in "The Odyssey". Some are even convinced that Gozo is the Island of Ogygia and the cave to be the one where the beautiful nymph Calypso kept Odysseus as a "prisoner of love" for seven years.
